#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:657
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reconciliation"
msgstr "Usklađivanje"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:658
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "At some point you will want to reconcile the transactions you have "
#| "entered with the transactions listed in a statement, be it a bank "
#| "statement, credit card statement, loan statement, or any other statement. "
#| "Reconciliation involves matching what you have entered with what the "
#| "statement lists. If any discrepancies are found then either you or the "
#| "person who created the statement have made a mistake."
msgid ""
"At some point, you will want to reconcile your records and details of an "
"account with the actual account to assure they match. This is generally done "
"by comparing the account in &kmymoney; with a printed or electronic "
"statement for the account issued by the institution, such as bank, credit "
"card, loan, or any other statement. Reconciliation involves matching what "
"you have entered, specifically the transactions since the previous "
"reconciliation, with what the statement lists. If any discrepancies are "
"found, either you or the person who created the statement has made a mistake."
msgstr ""
"U nekom trenutku ćete željeti uskladiti transakcije koje ste unijeli sa "
"transakcijama koje su izlistane u izvještaju, bilo bankovnom izvještaju, "
"bilo izvještaju kreditne kartice, kreditnom izvještaju ili bilo kojem "
"drugom. Usklađivanje uključuje povezivanje onoga što ste unijeli sa onim što "
"je izlistano u izvještajima. Ako se pojave određene nedosljednosti, onda ste "
"pogriješili ili vi, ili osoba koja je kreirala izvještaj."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:669
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To reconcile an account, first select the account, either from "
#| "<guiicon>Accounts</guiicon> view or from <guiicon>Ledgers</guiicon> view. "
#| "Then, either click on the <guiicon>Reconcile</guiicon> icon on the "
#| "Toolbar, or select <guimenuitem>Reconcile</guimenuitem> from the "
#| "<guimenu>Account</guimenu> menu."
msgid ""
"To reconcile an account, first select the account, either from the "
"<guiicon>Accounts</guiicon> View or in the <guiicon>Ledgers</guiicon> View. "
"Then, either click the <guiicon>Reconcile</guiicon> icon on the Toolbar, if "
"it is visible, or select the <menuchoice><guimenu>Account</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Reconcile</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Da biste uskladili račun, prvo odaberite račun, iz pregleda <guiicon>Računi</"
"guiicon> ili iz pregleda <guiicon>Finansijske knjige</guiicon>. Onda, ili "
"kliknite na ikonu <guiicon>Uskladi</guiicon> u alatnoj traci, ili odaberite "
"<guimenuitem>Uskladi</guimenuitem> iz menija <guimenu>Račun</guimenu> ."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:677
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "A full description of this topic can be found in the <link linkend="
#| "\"details.reconcile\">Reconciliation</link> section."
msgid ""
"A more detailed description of this topic can be found in the <link linkend="
"\"details.reconcile\">Reconciliation</link> section."
msgstr ""
"Puni opis ove teme može biti pronađen u dijelu <link linkend=\"details."
"reconcile\">Usklađivanje</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:683
#, no-c-format
msgid "Backing up"
msgstr "Rezervne kopije"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:684
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Now that you have created some accounts and entered transactions it's a "
#| "good idea to perform a backup. Because the file used by &kappname; is a "
#| "standard Unix file you can just copy the file to another location to back "
#| "it up or use the dialog provided by &kappname;. Using the dialog is the "
#| "preferred method because if &kappname; ever starts using other file "
#| "formats, such as SQL, then it would be much harder to copy the file "
#| "manually."
msgid ""
"Now that you have created some accounts and entered transactions it's a good "
"idea to perform a backup. Because the file used by &kmymoney; is a standard "
"&Linux; file (or &macOS; or &Windows; file, depending on your operating "
"system) you can just copy the file to another location to back it up or use "
"the dialog provided by &kmymoney;. Using the dialog is the preferred method "
"because if &kmymoney; ever starts using other file formats, such as SQL, "
"then it would be much harder to copy the file manually."
msgstr ""
"Sada kada ste kreirali neke račune i unijeli transakcije, dobra je ideja da "
"napravite rezervne kopije. Datoteka koju koristi &kappname; je standardna "
"UNIX datoteka, stoga je možete jednostavno kopirati na drugu lokaciju da "
"biste napravili rezervu ili koristiti dijalog koji pruža &kappname;. "
"Korištenje dijaloga je preferirana opcija jer ako &kappname; ikada počne "
"koristiti datoteke drugih formata kao što je SQL, onda bi bilo mnogo teže "
"kopirati datoteke ručno."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:694
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To backup your file through &kappname; Select <guimenuitem>Backup</"
#| "guimenuitem> from the <guimenu>File</guimenu> menu and enter the folder "
#| "where you wish the file to be copied to. If the folder needs mounting "
#| "first and you have the sufficient privileges then check the tick box "
#| "labeled <guilabel>Mount this directory before backing up</guilabel> and "
#| "click on <guibutton>OK</guibutton>."
msgid ""
"To backup your file through &kmymoney; Select <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Backup</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item and enter "
"the folder where you wish the file to be saved. If the folder needs mounting "
"first and you have the sufficient privileges then check the tick box labeled "
"<guilabel>Mount this folder before backing up</guilabel> and click "
"<guibutton>OK</guibutton>."
msgstr ""
"Da biste napravili rezervnu kopiju datoteke kroz &kappname; odaberite "
"<guimenuitem>Rezervna kopija</guimenuitem> iz <guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> "
"menija i unesite direktorij gdje želite kopirati datoteku. Ako direktorij "
"prvo treba kreirati i imata dovoljne privilegije onda zakačite okvir "
"naslovljen sa <guilabel>Kreiraj ovaj direktorij prije pravljenja rezervne "
"kopije</guilabel> i kliknite na <guibutton>OK</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:703
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The file will be copied to the folder specified with the current date "
#| "appended to the filename so it is easy to see the date the file was "
#| "backed up."
msgid ""
"The file will be saved to the folder specified with the current date "
"appended to the filename so it is easy to see the date the file was backed "
"up."
msgstr ""
"Datoteka će biti kopirana u direktorij određen trenutnim datuom priloženim "
"imenu datoteku tako da je jednostavno vidjeti datum kada je napravljena "
"rezervna kopija datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:708
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more details about the actual format of the data file, and the backup "
"process, see the <link linkend=\"details.formats\">File Formats</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:714
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Launching &kappname;"
msgid "Launching &kmymoney;"
msgstr "Pokretanje &kappname;-a"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:715
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Most commonly, you will launch &kappname; from an icon or a start menu of "
#| "your window manager. In this case, the default behavior is that "
#| "&kappname; will open the last file you had open. However, in some "
#| "circumstances, you will want or need to launch &kappname; from the "
#| "command line."
msgid ""
"Most commonly, you will launch &kmymoney; from an icon or a start menu of "
"your window manager or desktop environment. In this case, the default "
"behavior is that &kmymoney; will open the last file you had open. However, "
"in some circumstances, you will want or need to launch &kmymoney; from the "
"command line."
msgstr ""
"Najčešće ćete pokrenuti &kappname; pomoću ikone iz start menija ili vašeg "
"upravitelja prozorima. U ovom slučaju, unaprijed određeno ponašanje je da će "
"&kappname; otvoriti posljednju datoteku koju ste otvarali. Međutim, u nekim "
"okolnostima, željet ćete ili ćete morati pokrenuti &kappname; iz komandne "
"linije."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:722
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "For a complete description of all the available line options, see the man "
#| "page for &kappname;. However, there are two special cases which we "
#| "describe here."
msgid ""
"For a complete description of all the available command line options, see "
"the man page for &kmymoney;. However, there are two special cases which we "
"describe here."
msgstr ""
"Za potpun opis svih dostupnih opcija linije, pogledajte glavnu stranicu za "
"&kappname;. Međutim, postoje dva specijalna slučaja koje ćemo opisati ovdje."

#. Tag: command
#: firsttime.docbook:728
#, no-c-format
msgid "kmymoney -n"
msgstr "kmymoney -n"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:729
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The -n option tells &kappname; not to open the last file it had open. "
#| "This can be useful if the program crashes on startup."
msgid ""
"The -n option tells &kmymoney; not to open the last file it had open. This "
"can be useful if the program crashes on startup."
msgstr ""
"-n opcija govori &kappname;-u da ne otvara datoteku koja je zadnja otvarana. "
"Ovo može biti korisno ako se program krahira prilikom startanja."

#. Tag: command
#: firsttime.docbook:735
#, no-c-format
msgid "kmymoney &lt;path to file&gt;"
msgstr "kmymoney &lt;path to file&gt;"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:736
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Giving &kappname; a filename on the command line tells it to open that "
#| "file instead of the last file it had open. You can use the name of any "
#| "valid &kappname; file, as described in the chapter on <link linkend="
#| "\"details.formats\">file formats</link>. In addition, this can be used to "
#| "import a <link linkend=\"details.impexp.gnucash\">GnuCash</link> file."
msgid ""
"Giving &kmymoney; a filename on the command line tells it to open that file "
"instead of the last file it had open. You can use the name of any valid "
"&kmymoney; file, as described in the chapter on <link linkend=\"details."
"formats\">file formats</link>. In addition, this can be used to import a "
"<link linkend=\"details.impexp.gnucash\">&gnucash;</link> file."
msgstr ""
"Unošenje imena datoteke u komandnoj liniju govori &kappname;-u da otvori tu "
"datoteku umjesto datoteke koja je zadnja otvarana. Možete koristiti ime bilo "
"koje validne &kappname; datoteke, što je opisano u poglavlju na <link "
"linkend=\"details.formats\">formati datoteka</link>. Dodatno, ovo može biti "
"korišteno za uvoz <link linkend=\"details.impexp.gnucash\">GnuCash</link> "
"datoteke."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:746
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "How to move &kappname; to a new computer"
msgid "How to move &kmymoney; to a new computer"
msgstr "Kako prebaciti &kappname; na novi kompjuter"

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:748
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving your data"
msgstr "Prebacivanje vaših podataka"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:749
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you get a new computer, it's very easy to move your data. In fact, all "
#| "you have to do is to copy your &kappname; data file. The name of the file "
#| "is shown in the title bar when &kappname; is running, it usually ends in ."
#| "kmy. The first time you run the application on the new computer you will "
#| "have to tell it where you have put the data file, either by running from "
#| "the command line, or from the <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Open...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu. You should "
#| "even be able to move between &Windows;, &MacOS;, and &Linux; systems."
msgid ""
"If you get a new computer, it's very easy to move your data. In fact, all "
"you have to do is to copy your &kmymoney; data file. The name of the file is "
"shown in the title bar when &kmymoney; is running; it usually ends in "
"<filename class=\"extension\">.kmy</filename>. The first time you run the "
"application on the new computer you will have to tell it where you have put "
"the data file, either by running from the command line, or from the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Open...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item. You should even be able to move between &Windows;, "
"&MacOS;, and &Linux; systems."
msgstr ""
"Ako kupite novi kompjuter, veoma je lako prebaciti sve podatke. Ustvari, sve "
"što trebate uraditi je kopirati vašu &kappname; datoteku podataka. Ime ove "
"datoteke je prikazano u naslovnom okviru kada je &kappname; pokrenut, obično "
"završava na .kmy. Kada prvi put pokrenete aplikaciju na novom kompjuteru "
"moraćete joj reći gdje ste spremili datoteku podataka, tako što je pokrenete "
"iz komandne linije, ili iz <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Otvori...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menija. Trebalo bi "
"biti moguće prebacivanje sa  &Windows;, &MacOS;, i &Linux; sistema."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:760
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have encrypted your data file, be sure the appropriate software and "
"keys have also been set up on the new computer."
msgstr ""
"Ako ste šifrirali vašu datoteku podataka, osigurajte se da su uspostavljeni "
"ključevi i odgovarajuči softver na novom računaru."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:765
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your data is in an SQL database, refer to documentation for your database "
"software for guidance on migrating your data."
msgstr ""
"Ako su vaši podaci SQL baza podataka, pogledajte dokumentaciju za softver "
"vaše baze podataka kako biste dobili upute za prebacivanje vaših podataka."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:770
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Note that this assumes you have installed the same version of &kappname; "
#| "on the new computer as you were running on the old computer. Installing a "
#| "newer version should also be safe, but you need to be aware of any issues "
#| "related to that upgrade. Any such issues should be noted in the release "
#| "notes for the new version."
msgid ""
"Note that this assumes you have installed the same version of &kmymoney; on "
"the new computer as you were running on the old computer. Installing a newer "
"version should also be safe, but you need to be aware of any issues related "
"to that upgrade. Any such issues should be noted in the release notes for "
"the new version."
msgstr ""
"Imajte na umu da ovo podrazumijeva da ste instalirali istu verziju "
"&kappname;-a na novom računaru koju ste koristili na starom. Instaliranje "
"novije verzije bi također trebalo biti sigurno, ali trebate biti svjesni "
"problema koji mogu nastati nadogradnjom. Bilo kakvi problemi te vrste bi "
"trebali biti zabilježeni u bilješkama za novu verziju."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:778
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving your settings"
msgstr "Prebacivanje vaših postavki"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:781
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you only move your data file to the new machine, as described in the "
#| "previous section, &kappname; will work correctly, but you will have lost "
#| "any settings you changed from the default on your old machine. To "
#| "maintain these settings, you also need to copy your configuration file. "
#| "This file is called <quote>kmymoneyrc</quote>. This file will be in a "
#| "directory with other &kde; application configuration files. On a &Linux; "
#| "system, this will be in <quote>$KDEHOME/share/config</quote> where <quote>"
#| "$KDEHOME</quote> is usually <quote>.kde4</quote> within your home "
#| "directory."
msgid ""
"If you only move your data file to the new machine, as described in the "
"previous section, &kmymoney; will work correctly, but you will have lost any "
"configuration settings you changed from the default on your old machine. To "
"maintain these settings, you also need to copy your configuration file. This "
"file is called <filename>kmymoneyrc</filename>. The location of this file "
"depends on your operating system and distribution. On a &Linux; system, this "
"will most likely be <filename class=\"directory\">.config</filename> within "
"your home folder. If you are migrating from a version of &kmymoney; prior to "
"5.0, the old location was <filename class=\"directory\">.kde4</filename>."
msgstr ""
"Ako pomjerite samo podatke na novi računar, kao što je opisano u prethodnom "
"dijelu, &kappname; će raditi ispravno, ali ćete izgubiti bilo kakve promjene "
"postavki u odnosu na unaprijed definisane. Da biste sačuvai te postavke, "
"također trebate kopirati datoteku konfiguracija. Ova datoteka se zove "
"<quote>kmymoneyrc</quote>. Ova datoteka će se nalaziti u direktoriju sa "
"ostalim &kde; aplikacijskim konfiguracionim datotekama. Na &Linux; sistemu, "
"nalazit će se u <quote>$KDEHOME/share/config</quote> gdje se <quote>"
"$KDEHOME</quote> obično nalazi <quote>.kde4</quote> u vašem početnom "
"direktoriju."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:793
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving plugin settings"
msgstr "Prebacivanje postavki dodataka"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:794
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you have run any &kappname; plugins, such as the csv importer or "
#| "exporter, it may also have created a configuration file in that same "
#| "directory, such as csvimporterrc or csvexporterrc. These should also be "
#| "copied to the new computer."
msgid ""
"If you have run any &kmymoney; plugin, such as the csv importer or exporter, "
"it may also have created a configuration file in that same folder, such as "
"<filename>csvimporterrc</filename> or <filename>csvexporterrc</filename>. "
"These files should also be copied to the new computer."
msgstr ""
"Ako ste pokrenuli bilo kakve &kappname; dodatke kao što je csv uvoznik ili "
"izvoznik, to je također možda kreiralo konfiguracionu datoteku, kao što su "
"csvimporterrc ili csvexporterrc. Ove datoteke bi također trebale biti "
"kopirane na vaš novi računar."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:801
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "As with the main data file, this assumes the same version of the plugin "
#| "on both computers. Upgrades are generally safe, but if the functionality "
#| "of the plugin has changed greatly, it is advisable to carefully test "
#| "using the old configuration file, to be sure the plugin behaves as you "
#| "expect."
msgid ""
"As with the main data file, this assumes the same version of the plugin on "
"both computers. Upgrades are generally safe, but if the functionality of the "
"plugin has changed greatly, it is advisable to carefully test using the old "
"configuration file, to be sure the plugin behaves as you expect. Of course "
"this applies even when upgrading the version of &kmymoney; on a single PC."
msgstr ""
"Kao što je slučaj i sa glavnom datotekom podataka, ovo podrazumijeva istu "
"verziju dodatka na oba računara. Nadogradnje su uglavnom sigurne, ali "
"ukoliko se funkcionalnost dodatka značajno promijenila, savjetuje se "
"pažljivo testiranje korištenjem stare konfiguracione datoteke, da se osigura "
"da se dodatak ponaša onako kako očekujete."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that when upgrading from a previous version to version 5.0 or higher, "
"the location of the template files used by the plugin for printing checks "
"has changed. Please consult the release notes or the project <ulink url="
"\"https://www.kmymoney.org/faq.php\">website</ulink> for more details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:817
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "These instructions are solely for moving your &kappname; data and "
#| "settings. However, there may be important items which are stored by &kde; "
#| "and not by &kappname;, such as any passwords stored in kwallet. Moving "
#| "other parts of your &kde; setup is beyond the scope of this manual, "
#| "although many of the relevant files are also stored under <quote>"
#| "$KDEHOME</quote>."
msgid ""
"These instructions are solely for moving your &kmymoney; data and settings. "
"However, there may be important items which are stored by &kde; and not by "
"&kmymoney;, such as passwords stored in Keychain. Moving other parts of your "
"&kde; setup is beyond the scope of this manual, although many of the "
"relevant files are also stored under <envar>$KDEHOME</envar>."
msgstr ""
"Ove upute su samo za prebacivanje vaših &kappname; podataka i postavki. "
"Međutim, moguće je da postoje važne stavke koje su pohranjene od strane "
"&kde;-a, ne od strane &kappname;-a, kao što su lozinke pohranjene u kwallet-"
"u. Prebacivanje ostalih dijelova vaših &kde; postavki izlazi izvan opsega "
"ovog priručnika, iako su mnoge releventne datoteke također pohranjene pod "
"<quote>$KDEHOME</quote>."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:829
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Contacting the Developers / Reporting Bugs"
msgid "Getting Help / Contacting the Developers / Reporting Bugs"
msgstr "Kontaktiranje razvojnih inženjera / Prijavljivanje grešaka"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:830
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since support channels change over time, you can refer to the <ulink url="
"\"https://kmymoney.org/support.html\">Support page</ulink> at the <ulink url="
"\"https://kmymoney.org/\">&kmymoney; web site</ulink> for the most up-to-"
"date information on where to get help with &kmymoney;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:837
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you simply have questions about using &kmymoney;, you want to confirm you "
"understanding of how the application works, or need assistance figuring out "
"the best way to handle a particular financial situation, please consider "
"using one of the information sources, forums, mailing lists, or chat "
"channels listed at the above link."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:845
#, no-c-format
msgid "Contacting the developers"
msgstr "Kontaktiranje razvojnih inženjera"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:846
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For general questions or comments about &kmymoney;, there is a users' "
"mailing list &userlist; with more details <ulink url=\"https://mail.kde.org/"
"mailman/listinfo/kmymoney\">here</ulink>. This list is suitable for general "
"questions and discussion. There is also a developers' mailing list &devlist; "
"with more details <ulink url=\"https://mail.kde.org/mailman/listinfo/"
"kmymoney-devel\">here</ulink>. This list is intended for more technical "
"discussions. Since replies are often sent only to the list, you may not get "
"any response unless you subscribe to the list you send to."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:858
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the developers generally monitor the various contact channels "
"mentioned above, so direct email contact is rarely necessary. However, we're "
"happy to hear about your experiences using &kmymoney; over whatever channel "
"you prefer."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:865
#, no-c-format
msgid "Reporting bugs"
msgstr "Prijava grešaka"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:866
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To report a bug please use the interface provided by &kappname; by "
#| "selecting <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>Report Bug</"
#| "guimenuitem></menuchoice> and filling in the required information. "
#| "However, in case you have any difficulties with that method, you can "
#| "report a bug (or file a wish-list or enhancement request) directly at the "
#| "<ulink url=\"http://bugs.kde.org\">&kde; bug reporting web page</ulink>. "
#| "Reports should be filed against the product <quote>kmymoney4</quote>. "
#| "<quote>kmymoney2</quote> was specifically for bugs in the 1.0.x versions "
#| "of the application, and as those versions are no longer supported, it is "
#| "closed for further bug reporting."
msgid ""
"To report a bug please use the interface provided by &kmymoney; by selecting "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>Report Bug</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item and filling in the required information. However, in "
"case you have any difficulties with that method, you can report a bug (or "
"file a wish-list or enhancement request) directly at the <ulink url="
"\"https://bugs.kde.org\">&kde; bug reporting web site</ulink>. Reports "
"should be filed against the product <quote>kmymoney</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Da biste prijavili grešku molimo koristite sučelje koje &kappname; pruža, "
"odabirom <menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoć</guimenu><guimenuitem>Prijavi grešku</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> i popunjavanjem neophodnih informacija. Međutim, u "
"slučaju da imate bilo kakvih poteškoća sa ovim načinom, možete prijaviti "
"grešku (ili poslati listu želja ili zahtjev za poboljšanje) na <ulink url="
"\"http://bugs.kde.org\">stranica prijavljivanja &kde; grešaka</ulink>. "
"Izvještaji bi trebali biti slani za proizvod <quote>kmymoney4</quote>. "
"<quote>kmymoney2</quote> je samo za greške u 1.0.x verzijama aplikacije, a "
"kako te verzije nisu više podržane, više nije otvoreno za prijavu grešaka."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:876
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In any case, before reporting a bug, please read through the guidelines "
#| "below. Following them will make it more likely that the developers will "
#| "be able to quickly identify the problem without having to ask you for "
#| "more information."
msgid ""
"In any case, before reporting a bug, please read through the guidelines "
"below. Following them will make it more likely that the developers will be "
"able to quickly identify the problem without having to ask you for more "
"information. Also try to be sure that what you are reporting really is a bug "
"(or wishlist/enhancement request.) If things are just not working they way "
"you expect, or you need help using some feature of &kmymoney;, please use "
"one of the alternate support channels listed above."
msgstr ""
"U svakom slučaju, prije prijave greške, molimo pročitajte upute ispod. "
"Praćenje njih će olakšati razvojnim inženjerima da brzo identifikuju problem "
"bez potrebe da pitaju vas za više informacija."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:886
#, no-c-format
msgid "Writing High Quality Bug Reports"
msgstr "Pisanje visoko kvalitetnih prijava grešaka"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:887
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We encourage users to take extra time to write high-quality bug reports when "
"submitting them. This reduces wasted effort on all sides, as the reporter "
"and the developer who will fix it trade emails until this information is "
"really in place."
msgstr ""
"Mi ohrabrujemo korisnike da potroše dodatnu količinu vremena za pisanje "
"visoko-kvalitetnih prijava grešaka. Ovo smanjuje utrošeni napor na svim "
"stranama, jer izvještač i razvojni inženjer koji će popravljati grešku "
"razmjenjuju email-ove sve dok se ova informacija ne nađe na pravom mjestu."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:894
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Eli Goldberg wrote the canonical Bug-Writing Guideline, available at "
#| "<ulink url=\"http://issues.apache.org/bugwritinghelp.html\">http://issues."
#| "apache.org/bugwritinghelp.html</ulink>. Generally, you'll be well-served "
#| "by following these guidelines:"
msgid ""
"Eli Goldberg wrote the canonical Bug-Writing Guideline, available at <ulink "
"url=\"https://issues.apache.org/bugwritinghelp.html\">https://issues.apache."
"org/bugwritinghelp.html</ulink>. Generally, you'll be well-served by "
"following the guidelines and advice from that page. Some of those points are "
"repeated below:"
msgstr ""
"Eli Goldberg je napisao kanonski oblik Pisanja grešaka, dostupan na <ulink "
"url=\"http://issues.apache.org/bugwritinghelp.html\">http://issues.apache."
"org/bugwritinghelp.html</ulink>. Generalno, izuzetno je koisno pratiti ove "
"upute."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:901
#, no-c-format
msgid "Include your system information"
msgstr "Uključi sistemske informacije"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:902
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>Report Bug</"
#| "guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu choice will fill this in automatically, "
#| "but if you would prefer not to use this interface, there are several "
#| "items you need to include in the report. We will need to know what "
#| "operating system you are using (&Linux;, &MacOS;, or &Windows;), the "
#| "version of &kde; and the version of &kappname; you're running, and either "
#| "the version of &MacOS; or &Windows; or the name and version of your "
#| "&Linux; distribution and the version of your kernel."
msgid ""
"The <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu><guimenuitem>Report Bug</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item will fill this in automatically, but if "
"you would prefer not to use this interface, there are several items you need "
"to include in the report. We will need to know what operating system you are "
"using (&Linux;, &MacOS;, or &Windows;), the version of &kde;, and the "
"version of &kmymoney; you're running, and either the version of &MacOS; or "
"&Windows; or the name and version of your &Linux; distribution and the "
"version of your kernel. This information is extremely important, as many "
"bugs (as well as behaviors mis-identified as bugs) depend on the Operating "
"System."
msgstr ""
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoć</guimenu><guimenuitem>Prijavi grešku</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> će ovo popuniti automatski, ali ako radije ne "
"biste koristili ovo sučelje, postoji više stavki koje trebate uključiti u "
"izvještaj. Trebat ćemo znati koji operativni sistem koristite (&Linux;, "
"&MacOS;, or &Windows;), verziju &kde;-a i verziju &kappname;-a koju "
"koristite, te ili verziju &MacOS; ili &Windows; ili ime i verziju vaše "
"&Linux; distribucije i verziju kernel-a."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:915
#, no-c-format
msgid "Include a backtrace for crashes"
msgstr "Uključi povratni trag za krahiranja"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:916
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The backtrace is often the single most useful piece of information in "
"solving crashes."
msgstr ""
"Povratni trag je najčešće najkorisnija informacija za rješavanje krahova."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:922
#, no-c-format
msgid "Try to reproduce it"
msgstr "Pokušajte ih reproducirati"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:923
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Let us know if you were able to do so. It's useful to know whether the "
#| "bug only happened once and you couldn't get it to happen again or happens "
#| "every time or happens sometimes but not others."
msgid ""
"Let us know if you were able to do so. It's useful to know whether the bug "
"only happened once and you couldn't get it to happen again or if it happens "
"every time or if it happens sometimes but not others."
msgstr ""
"Javite nam ako ste uspjeli to uraditi. Korisno je znati da li se grešla "
"desila samo jednom i niste je uspjeli ponoviti ili se nekad dešava, a nekad "
"ne."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:930
#, no-c-format
msgid "Include specific steps"
msgstr "Uključite specifične korake"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:931
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is a bad bug report: <quote>I entered a transaction, and &kappname; "
#| "crashed.</quote> A much better bug report is: <quote>Using the "
#| "transaction form, I entered a new transaction in my Credit Card account. "
#| "I selected the Transfer tab, entered in an amount, then changed to the "
#| "Deposit tab, and back to the Transfer tab. When I returned to the "
#| "Transfer tab, &kappname; crashed. This bug is fully reproducible for me.</"
#| "quote>"
msgid ""
"This is a bad bug report: <quote>I entered a transaction, and &kmymoney; "
"crashed.</quote> A much better bug report is: <quote>Using the transaction "
"form, I entered a new transaction in my Credit Card account. I selected the "
"Transfer tab, entered an amount, then changed to the Deposit tab, and back "
"to the Transfer tab. When I returned to the Transfer tab, &kmymoney; "
"crashed. This bug is fully reproducible for me.</quote>"
msgstr ""
"Ovo je loš izvještaj o grešci: <quote>Unio sam transakciju, i &kappname; se "
"krahirao.</quote> Mnogo bolji izvještaj o grešci je <quote>Korištenjem forme "
"za transakciju, unio sam novu transakciju u račun za kreditnu karticu. "
"Odabrao sam karticu Prebaci, unio iznos, onda sam se prebacio na karticu "
"Depozit , i vratio se na karticu Prebaci. Kada sam se vratio na karticu "
"Prebaci, &kappname; se krahirao. Ova greška mi se stalno dešava.</quote>"

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:941
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tell us what you expected to happen"
msgstr "Recite nam šta ste očekivali da se desi"

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:942
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In some cases, this is obvious, but in more subtle bugs, sometimes you'll "
#| "see a bug report where it is not obvious what the reporter expected to "
#| "happen. Always tell us what you think should have happened."
msgid ""
"In some cases, this is obvious, but in more subtle bugs, sometimes you'll "
"see a bug report where it is not obvious what the reporter expected to "
"happen. Always tell us what you think should have happened, as well as what "
"did happen."
msgstr ""
"U nekim situacijama, ovo je očigledno, ali kod suptilnijih grešaka, vidjet "
"ćete izvještaj u kojem nije jasno šta je podnosilac izvještaja očekivao da "
"se desi. Uvijek nam recite šta vi mislite, šta se trebalo dogoditi."

#. Tag: title
#: firsttime.docbook:949
#, no-c-format
msgid "Consider running with debugging enabled"
msgstr "Pokušajte pokrenuti sa debugging-om uključenim."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:950
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "By compiling a version configured with --enable-debug=full you can ensure "
#| "that the best possible backtraces are generated. If you encounter a "
#| "crash, run &kappname; again from within gdb, and reproduce the crash. "
#| "When it crashes, type <quote>bt</quote> to generate a backtrace."
msgid ""
"By compiling a version configured with --enable-debug=full you can ensure "
"that the best possible backtraces are generated. If you encounter a crash, "
"run &kmymoney; again from within gdb, and reproduce the crash. When it "
"crashes, type <quote>bt</quote> to generate a backtrace."
msgstr ""
"Kompajliranjem verzije konfigurasane sa --enable-debug=full možete se "
"osigurati da su generisani najbolji povratni tragovi. Ako naletite na krah, "
"pokrenite &kappname; ponovo iz gdb-a, i reproducirajte krah. Kada se "
"krahira, unesite <quote>bt</quote> za generisanje povratnog traga."

#. Tag: para
#: firsttime.docbook:958
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Running this way is a bit more difficult, so we don't expect all users to "
#| "do this. However, if you're interested in helping &kappname; become as "
#| "stable as possible, this is the best way to do it short of finding the "
#| "bug in the code and sending in a patch."
msgid ""
"Running this way is a bit more difficult, so we don't expect all users to do "
"this. However, if you're interested in helping &kmymoney; become as stable "
"as possible, this is the best way to do it short of finding the bug in the "
"code and sending in a patch."
msgstr ""
"Pokretanje na ovaj način je malo teže, tako da ne očekujemo od svih "
"korisnika da urade ovo. Međutim, ako ste zainteresovani da pomognete "
"&kappname;-u da postanje što je moguće stabilniji, ovo je najbolji način da "
"uradite ovo. Jedini bolji način od ovog je da nađete grešku u kodu i "
"pošaljete ispravak."

